Azure Log Analytics collects and analyzes log data from various resources. It provides deep insights into system behavior and performance.

Users can run queries to analyze logs and detect issues.

For example, administrators can analyze logs to identify failed login attempts or system errors.

A real-life use case is security monitoring, where suspicious activities are detected through log analysis.

Another example is troubleshooting application issues by analyzing logs.

Log Analytics enables data-driven decision-making and advanced diagnostics.
